-- Mountain Collapse in Sichuan Province Leaves at Least 16 Dead, Xinhua Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-15T02:57:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/mountain-collapse-in-sichuan-province-leaves-at-least-16-dead-xinhua-says.html

          
          
             A mountain collapsed in southwest
China early today, leaving at least 16 people dead and seven
injured, the official Xinhua news agency reported, citing the
local government.  
 The accident happened in Kangding county in the Ganzi
Tibetan region of Sichuan province at about 1:25 a.m., the
agency said. The collapse crushed work sheds at a construction
site according to the regionâ€™s public emergency command center,
Xinhua said.  
 Rescue work is underway and local authorities are
investigating the cause of the collapse, according to the
report.  
          
          


  


        